//@version=6
// ============================================================================
// Market Tradability Engine v2 [WavesUnchained]
// Version: 2.2.1
// Author: WavesUnchained
// Build: 2026-07-16
// ============================================================================
// Market quality and no-trade filter - v2 research build.
//
// v1 (market_tradability_engine.pine) drives its eight-state market machine
// from four scores: Tradability, Balance, Compression, Direction. v2 is a
// parallel rearchitecture that reduces those four to three fundamental
// market properties, and derives every state from combinations of them:
//
//   STRUCTURE  (0-100)     - is there a coherent framework right now, either
//                            a respected range or a clean trend?
//   ENERGY     (0-100)     - is movement intensity building or fading -
//                            volatility, momentum acceleration, candle
//                            commitment, and how efficiently it converts
//                            into net progress?
//   ACCEPTANCE (-100..100) - are new prices being validated (held) or
//                            rejected (wicked away), and which way?
//
// States (same eight as v1, now derived from Structure/Energy/Acceptance):
//   NO TRADE   - no coherent structure (chaos or a dead market)
//   BALANCE    - range-flavored structure, low energy, neutral acceptance
//   COMPRESSION- balance plus energy contracted further
//   READY      - compression plus energy building off its trough plus
//                acceptance pressure near a boundary
//   BREAKOUT   - price held beyond the boundary for several bars with
//                energy and acceptance both confirming
//   TREND      - trend-flavored structure, high energy, strong acceptance
//   AFTERMATH  - energy and acceptance were both recently strong but energy
//                has since collapsed - the impulse went quiet
//   EXHAUSTION - extended trend showing energy decay, rising rejection
//                wicks, or a volatility spike
//
// This is a Beta / parallel research build, not a replacement for v1.
// Thresholds are carried over analogously from v1 where a direct mapping
// exists, but are not yet calibrated against real data - run the
// calibration log for both indicators side by side before trusting v2 over
// v1 on any specific instrument.
//
// Main outputs:
//   Structure Score    0-100
//   Energy Score       0-100
//   Acceptance Score  -100 to +100
//
// Features:
//   ✓ Three fundamental scores (Structure / Energy / Acceptance) replace
//     v1's four (Tradability / Balance / Compression / Direction)
//   ✓ Eight-state market machine with disagreement-streak confirmation and
//     minimum-duration hysteresis (same mechanics as v1)
//   ✓ Breakout acceptance (multi-bar hold), Ready energy-building check and
//     post-breakout Balance lock are first-class parts of the model here,
//     not add-on patches
//   ✓ Leaner six-row dashboard (down from v1's nine rows)
//   ✓ Ratio-based scores are ranked against their own recent history
//     (percentile rank) instead of fixed constants, so the same defaults
//     generalize across timeframes and instruments
//   ✓ Reactivity preset (Early / Balanced / Conservative / Custom) tunes how
//     readily states change - thresholds and confirmation/duration bars -
//     independent of the lookback-length Preset
//   ✓ Baseline Type selector (EMA/SMA/RMA/WMA/SuperSmoother/T3/KAMA/JMA
//     Approx) for the Quality Baseline, matching the advanced-smoothing
//     pattern from wavetrend_advanced_smoothing.pine
//   ✓ Pine-Log calibration logging (config snapshot, per-bar raw scores,
//     state-transition context), event-prefixed MTE2 so it can run
//     side-by-side with v1's MTE log on the same chart
//
// This indicator does not generate unconditional buy/sell signals.
// Breakout markers identify a market-state transition, not a complete setup.
// ============================================================================

indicator(
     "Market Tradability Engine v2 [WavesUnchained]",
     shorttitle = "MTE v2",
     overlay = true,
     max_labels_count = 200
)

// ============================================================================
// CONSTANTS
// ============================================================================

